about.summary: A collection of various oversampling techniques developed from SMOTE is provided. SMOTE is a oversampling technique which synthesizes a new minority instance between a pair of one minority instance and one of its K nearest neighbor. (see <https://www.jair.org/media/953/live-953-2037-jair.pdf> for more information) Other techniques adopt this concept with other criteria in order to generate balanced dataset for class imbalance problem.

name: r-smotefamily
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.3.1' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-smotefamily
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/smotefamily_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/smotefamily/smotefamily_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 978d99afaf1bfe51d1752f652298a5e2e1fde2f667e10f8373dee2158ebe5e18

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 3
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-fnn
    - r-dbscan
    - r-igraph
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-fnn
    - r-dbscan
    - r-igraph

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('smotefamily')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('smotefamily')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=smotefamily
  license: GPL (>= 3)
  summary: A collection of various oversampling techniques developed from SMOTE is provided.
    SMOTE is a oversampling technique which synthesizes a new minority instance between
    a pair of one minority instance and one of its K nearest neighbor. (see <https://www.jair.org/media/953/live-953-2037-jair.pdf>
    for more information) Other techniques adopt this concept with other criteria in
    order to generate balanced dataset for class imbalance problem.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
